The National Hajj Commission of Nigeria (NAHCON) has revealed that the first set of Nigerians to depart the country for the 2022 hajj in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia would begin their journey on June 9. The Chairman of NAHCON, Zikirullah Hassan, made the announcement on Friday in Abuja while speaking at the signing of the 2022 hajj airlift agreement. According to him, the date is to allow for adequate preparation for the Nigerians during the period. He stated that the three airlines selected for the exercise are Azman Air, Max Air and Flynas Airlines.